1.title: Plenty of Fish in the Big D
1.plot: Following another night working the red carpet, young philanthropist Tara Harper picks up the newest rescue dogs from a local shelter. In his down time during the NFL lockout, punter Glenn Pakulak thrusts himself into the world of fitness modeling, showing off the good looks he's been blessed with. Drama ensues when the gang meets the latest addition to Matt's blond-tourage -- a gorgeous singer and single mom, Neill Skyler, who just moved back into town.

2.title: Take the Bulls by the Horns
2.plot: Drew dives head first into the dating world with the help of a matchmaker, while Tara gives it a go with a popular Texas radio host. Courtney picks herself up by the bootstraps and agrees to resolve the awkward first meeting with Neill. Matt enters uncharted territory spending time with a single mom, but still finds himself in a more familiar setting on a dinner date with a triad of beautiful women.

3.title: When Pigs Fly
3.plot: Courtney tries one last time to rectify things with Neill, yet her motive is still just to appease Matt. Drew shells out the big bucks on Glenn at a charity date auction, but has other plans for his favorite muscle-bound bachelor. Courtney joins in on the fun and suddenly sees Glenn in a different light.

4.title: Make Love Not War
4.plot: Drew tries to win back the heart of an old flame by bringing him to brunch at the Ginsburg mansion. Things get really awkward when Neill struggles to connect with Glenn's football buddy while Glenn moves in on her brunette bestie. The gang comes together to support Drew as the co-chair of one of Dallas' largest black-tie fundraisers.

5.title: Getting to Know You
5.plot: After their blowout, Drew and Courtney attempt to resolve their differences. Matt and Neill discover their feelings for one another may be deeper than they're willing to admit. Drew's ex drops a bomb on him, disrupting Drew's plans to win him back. Courtney moves into foreign territory with a hottie from South Africa, as Glenn reconnects with a former love interest. Meanwhile, Tara learns that kids may not be in the future plans of the man she is dating.

6.title: Friendly as Fire Ants
6.plot: Courtney accepts an awkward double date invite from Matt. Meanwhile, the chemistry between Glenn and his ex-flame continues to heat up, even as she plans to heads back to San Francisco. At the tasting for Matt's charity event, things get heated when he offers six-years-sober Drew a cocktail. Then, the whole group attends a concert, where it's Courtney's attitude that takes a turn for the worse.

7.title: Everythings Bigger in Texas
7.plot: After the concert, Matt calls Courtney out on her poor attitude. Glenn exposes his softer side to his ex-girlfriend before she heads back to the west coast. Tara continues her streak of serial monogamy, as things get serious with Jody. Meanwhile, Drew confides in his close friend Daylon about a big mistake that may ruin his chances of ever getting back together with Cody. Matt prepares for his first Leadership Gala, and with a guest list encompassing UT's most famous Longhorns and Dallas' brightest starlets, anxiety is running high -- and his best girl is running late.

8.title: Pony Up
8.plot: Drew makes a last-ditch effort to win back Cody's heart before he leaves for New York. Tara and Jody head to Fort Worth for an unforgettable date. A relaxing weekend off the grid forces Courtney and Matt to test the boundaries of their friendship in the enchanting Texas hillside. With the NFL lockout looming and Rebecca weighing heavy on his heart, Glenn struggles with the decision to move to Oakland. plot: Follows a group of successful friends, from beauty queens to pro-football players, living it up like only Texas socialites can.::Anonymous
